description:
You are a corporate flight dispatcher preparing a briefing for a charter flight to the Colorado Rockies. Collect technical facility data for Aspen-Pitkin County (KASE), Telluride Regional (KTEX), and Eagle County Regional (KEGE) using AirNav. Create a browser bookmark folder named 'Mountain Airports' containing the AirNav pages for each airport. Download the 'LOC/DME-E' (or 'LOC/DME-E (SPECIAL)') approach plate PDF for KASE to the Downloads folder. Document the elevation (ft), longest runway dimensions (ft), primary CTAF or Tower frequency, and responsible ARTCC for all three airports in a JSON file at ~/Documents/airport_briefing.json.

The JSON structure must be:
{
  "briefing_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "airports": {
    "KASE": { "elevation_ft": 0, "longest_runway": "", "frequency_mhz": 0.0, "artcc": "" },
    "KTEX": { "elevation_ft": 0, "longest_runway": "", "frequency_mhz": 0.0, "artcc": "" },
    "KEGE": { "elevation_ft": 0, "longest_runway": "", "frequency_mhz": 0.0, "artcc": "" }
  }
}
